  "text": "APPENDIX II PREDICTION WITH RK4 Given a the system's generalized coordinates q t and generalized velocityq t at some time t, we wish to predict q t ′ andq t ′ at some time t ′ = t + ∆t. First, we define x t = [q t ,q t ] ⊤ , and consequently,ẋ t = [q t ,q t ] ⊤ . Here,q t is computed according to Equation [CITATION_1] . To integrate a function g(x, u), RK4 is a standard integration scheme: k 1 = ∆t · g(x t , u t ) k 2 = ∆t · g(x t + k 1 /2, u t ) k 3 = ∆t · g(x t + k 2 /2, u t ) k 4 = ∆t · g(x t + k 3 , u t )",
